Abstract: The problem considered is that of the firm that must choose from a set of feasible borrowing sources that includes foreign as well as domestic sources. Expressions are developed for the effective cost of borrowing under conditions of inflation and devaluation and under the condition of either local or foreign ownership of the firm. One simple decision rule is shown to be sufficient for choosing an international borrowing source, and this rule is compared with-a rule from the literature.&copy; 1973 JIBS. Journal of International Business Studies (1973) 4, 97&ndash;104
